(ADG&rsquo;s description:)

The Millenium World in Flames Annual is Australian Design Group's latest greatest Annual. It is jam packed with all the latest tips and hints for all our World in Flames products.

It includes:
&bull; an America in Flames after action replay;
&bull; a new political system for World in Flames;
&bull; the latest strategy hints for World in Flames;
&bull; latest optional rules for World in Flames;
&bull; integrated Vichy and conquest system;
&bull; in depth Patton in Flames strategy notes;
&bull; four new campaign (Operation Star Spangled banner, The Bear Unleashed, The Duce's dream and Race to be a Superpower) set-up and notes;
&bull; 200 Politics in Flames counters that includes the political markers for Politics in Flames, heavy weapons units for Russia and China, warlord counters, friction markers, new carriers that include surface to air missiles, partisan headquarters, late war Soviet jets and night fighters, etc.; and
&bull; the centrepiece of the Annual, Politics in Flames.

Politics in Flames allows you to economically, politically and militarily bring minor countries into your sphere of interest during the critical years of World War II. Can you woo Czechoslovakia, Spain, Turkey and Brazil amongst dozens of other countries to help you in your war of liberation?

The Millenium World in Flames Annual includes 200 counters, a 76 page Annual and the latest edition (&copy; 2000) combat charts.

from poeppelkiste.de:

One player uses magnetic force & an ornery witches broom to move his magic crystals across the board and into the cauldron. At the same time, another player rolls dice as the Guardian of Time in order to stop the player turn. Whoever gets four crystals in first wins the game.

from HABA website:
All the witches have gathered for the duel with the jinxed broom Mumbo Jumbo. Each one tries to tame the flying broom and make it sweep their magic gems into the cauldron. However, only the one who has a magic touch with the witch's magnetic power will be the first to be able to sweep his magic gems into the cauldron.

Quadrix - The MONEY For WORDS Game

"Quadrix is an exciting new idea in word games; A perfect blend of skill and luck" David Prinz (On Box Cover)

From the Rules:

The object of the game is to win money from other players through the use of word-building skills. You can make money in four ways:
(a) By completing legal words on the word board through placement of letter tiles;
(b) By placing letter tiles which may contribute towards legal words on the word board;
(c) By challenging an opponent who then fails to prove that the letter tiles they placed on the word board can lead to legal words;
(d) By proving to a challenger that the letter tiles you added to the word board can lead to legal words.

Publisher Blurb:

This tactical sourcebook explores the various theaters of the early days of the Alternate Second World War and the operations that took place in them. Fields of War contains numerous tactical scenario seeds for the Gear Krieg universe that can be played together or separately, along with sample strike forces and heroes, special rules and miniature modeling advice for both the tabletop and the Gear Krieg miniatures.

Fields of War includes:

- Rules for Natural, Urban and Combat Engineering tabletop features; 
- Scenario seeds for the above environments; 
- Modeling instructions for both the tabletop and miniatures; 
- New Heroes and equipment for Germany, the British Commonwealth, the United States, Soviet Russia and Imperial Japan; 
- and several new vehicles and variants.

A copy of the Gear Krieg Rulebook, a few six-sided dice, miniatures/counters, pen and paper are required to use this supplement.
